last_episode_to_air.name: Fire knives don't carve
last_episode_to_air.overview: Professor Dimitris Lainis puts all the pieces of the puzzle together, while the police receive an unexpected proposal that causes moral dilemmas. Everyone is held accountable for their actions and punishment meets justice. "Nemesis" is coming for everyone.

name: The Other Me
overview: A series of murders alarm the police authorities, as strange symbolisms are traced to every crime scene. The eccentric professor of criminology Dimitris Lainis is asked to shed some light on the mystery.

seasons.name: Lost Souls
seasons.overview: A series of murders alarms the police authorities, as unknown symbols are found at the scene of each crime. When all the data of the investigation around the perpetrator outline the profile of a serial killer, the eccentric professor of criminology, Dimitris Lainis (Pygmalion Dadakaridis) is recruited once again. The professor is called to find the link between the continuous murders, the meaning of the symbols and solve another mystery.

seasons.name: Catharsis
seasons.overview: In the 8-episode cycle of "The Other Me: Catharsis", a new series of murders with female victims comes to shake up the University circles. Criminology professor Dimitris Lainis is facing the police authorities, as the main suspect is considered to be the candidate for Rector, his collaborator and friend, Elias Velissaratos, played by Konstantinos Markoulakis. As the story unfolds, the upheavals follow one another and a well-established plot that connects all the hypotheses begins to surface.

episodes.name: Shattered Mind
episodes.overview: A brutal murder alarms the police authorities. With the investigation leading to confusing controversies, the eccentric professor of criminology Dimitris Lainis is asked to shed some light on the mystery.

episodes.name: Something Goes, Something Comes
episodes.overview: A woman is found mysteriously murdered. Soon her identity is revealed, but the enigma surrounding the circumstances of her tragic death remains unsolved. A female eyewitness might give some answers.

episodes.name: On the Trails of the Myths
episodes.overview: The number of victims keeps rising, leading to more questions and confusion. While the police interrogations go on, Dimitris Lainis is looking for clues in the most unlikely source: The Feats of Theseus.

episodes.name: Mighty Castles Are Defeated from Inside
episodes.overview: While the police investigations continue, Dimitris Lainis examines the details of Theseus' Feats in his attempt to decipher the enigma. Developments, however, surpass him. One more feat gets 'checkmarked'.

episodes.name: Waiting for the Dead to Speak
episodes.overview: The police authorities 'return' to the first crime scene, looking for new clues. In the meantime, Barasopoulos decides to engage Christina in the case, so they can both benefit from their collaboration.

episodes.name: Unity Makes Strength
episodes.overview: While the investigations continue, Barasopoulos and Christina agree on the usefulness of an urgent news bulletin. Their aim is to upset the elusive perpetrator and lead him to a revealing mistake.

episodes.name: Ariadne's Thread
episodes.overview: New leads draw Dimitris and Barasopoulos ever closer to the elusive culprit and lead them to an alarming conclusion. Will they be able to predict the perpetrator's dramatic next move before it's too late?

episodes.name: Irrational Logic
episodes.overview: In the dramatic last episode, the police authorities race against time to locate the perpetrator and put an end to his killing spree. Will they succeed in solving the mystery and finally closing the case?

1.name: Lost Souls
1.overview: A series of murders alarms the police authorities, as unknown symbols are found at the scene of each crime. When all the data of the investigation around the perpetrator outline the profile of a serial killer, the eccentric professor of criminology, Dimitris Lainis (Pygmalion Dadakaridis) is recruited once again. The professor is called to find the link between the continuous murders, the meaning of the symbols and solve another mystery.

episodes.name: The Third Candidate
episodes.overview: The mysterious murder of a female student causes unrest in university circles. With a close suspect, a close associate and friend, Professor Dimitris Lainis hastens to unravel the mystery.

episodes.name: New World Order
episodes.overview: Investigations into the murder have begun. And while the new Deputy Chief is determined to change everything, a mysterious file reaches the hands of the Director of Police Laboratories.

episodes.name: Daughter of Forkeas
episodes.overview: Continuing the search for the murdered student, the police take DNA and fingerprints from the professors and the university staff. The pressure peaks when a new corpse is discovered.

episodes.name: Enemies Within Gates
episodes.overview: The two victims have one thing in common: a tattoo on Medusa's head. Later, after his visit to the University, Lieutenant Sklavis finds a note with the name of a girl.

episodes.name: A New Alliance
episodes.overview: Everything shows that the organization continues its activities. And while Christina is doing an interview in prison, the police visit the mother of the murdered student. Is there any new evidence of her death.

episodes.name: King Under Threat
episodes.overview: A new suitor for the position of the leader of the organization makes his appearance. Meanwhile, police officer Carra continues the investigation, while a creepy video reaches the hands of Velissaratos.

episodes.name: The Three Packages
episodes.overview: While Lainis learns about the video, journalist Stergiou risks her life again. Meanwhile, the police continue the investigations and the unexpected meeting of two members of the organization brings upset.

episodes.name: An Unbearable Victory
episodes.overview: All the pieces of the puzzle are in place. All that is missing is the arrest of the culprits and the identification of the Reptile. A voluntary testimony will lead the police to a meeting with him, in the subversive finale.

As the story unfolds, the upheavals follow one another and a well-established plot that connects all the hypotheses begins to surface.

episodes.name: The beginning of the end
episodes.overview: While Athena becomes the new Head of Homicide and Dimitris mourns the loss of his beloved Tonia, a deadly explosion forces the Department to regroup and take action.

episodes.name: The return of the prodigal
episodes.overview: The crisis in Apostolos's relationship with Eleni escalates. At the same time, while the police interrogate those involved in the explosion, the appearance of people from the past complicates things even more.

episodes.name: The past returns
episodes.overview: Danae is visiting Laini, who has now returned to his teaching duties and reveals her plans in relation to the "other me" case. Athena solves the case of 18 -year -old Melina. Masatos is in the hospital after Vanorta's attack. At the same time, a second case of homicide occurs, while the police are dealing with the explosion in the funeral home.

episodes.name: The immortality of dreams
episodes.overview: While Tonya's father demands answers, Christina accepts a proposal from Danae. At the same time, the police investigation into the explosion and the identification of Staikos has reached an impasse.

episodes.name: The cry of the dead
episodes.overview: Forensic results turn everything upside down in the explosion case, leading to yet another impasse. Faced with new information, the police implement a plan to shake things up.

episodes.name: Water turbid and uneducated soul does not see turmoil
episodes.overview: An unlikely alliance is born as the police's plan fails, forcing Laini to become involved in the investigation. Meanwhile, the authorities are informed of another murder.

episodes.name: Α man's character is his fate
episodes.overview: The police finally achieve a major breakthrough in their investigation, thanks to the help of not only Dimitris Lainis but also some unexpected allies.
